   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The independent static bypass switch (ISBS) is an option,
when triggered it is called ISBS operation. In ISBS operation the
system is locked in static bypass by the ISBS solution. ISBS operation
can be triggered if the main controller is inoperable and unable to
switch over to bypass operation.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">From ISBS operation it is not
possible to switch to another operating mode because the correct function
of the system cannot be guaranteed. To switch back to normal operation
the system must be switched to manual bypass and then restarted. For
more information see the chapter <xref href="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_ISS_or_ISBS_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_DD00545783.dita"
                  scope="local"
                  type="concept"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
